<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-041-004 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 440 495</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDN  Oct 1 1991 v36 n20 p77(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Generator owes accuracy and versatility to DSP andarbitrary-waveform technology. (Analogic Corp.'s 2030 functiongenerator uses digital signal processing technology)(EDN Editors'Choice) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Strassberg, Dan.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Analogic Corp's 2030 function generator can be used to producecomplicated waveforms as simply as classical generators outputsine, square and triangular waves.andP;  The product uses digitalsignal processing (DSP) technology to produce waveforms withunusually low distortion and few artifacts; it also predistortsthe samples fed to its digital-to-analog converter to compensatefor sampling effects and the transient response of theanti-imaging filter that follows the converter.andP;  A Motorola 56001DSP microprocessor in the unit executes algorithmic routinesstored in ROM and fills the device's dual-port memory with samplesrepresenting the output waveforms.andP;  The compactness of thealgorithms when compared to point-by-point signal representationsmeans more waveforms can be stored.andP;  The 12-bit-resolutionarbitrary-waveform generator included lets the $3,995 unitsynthesize signals that are not in its library and that cannot beproduced by manipulating the library functions.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Analogic Corp. (Innovations).andO;Ticker:    ALOG.andO;Product:   Analogic 2030 (Test equipment, electronic) (Innovations).andO;Topic:     Function GeneratorsNew TechniqueWaveformsAutomatic test equipmentAnalog integrated circuitsSignal processing.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>